Here's the recommended approach:

**1. Abstract the HTTP dependency**

```csharp
// In your MCP server project
public interface IApiClient
{
    Task<OrderResult> GetOrderAsync(int id);
}

public class ApiClient : IApiClient
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;
    public ApiClient(HttpClient http) => _http = http;
    public async Task<OrderResult> GetOrderAsync(int id) =>
        await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<OrderResult>($"/orders/{id}");
}
```

**2. Inject it into your tool class**

```csharp
public class OrderTool
{
    private readonly IApiClient _api;
    public OrderTool(IApiClient api) => _api = api;

    public async Task<string> GetOrder(int id)
    {
        var order = await _api.GetOrderAsync(id);
        return $"Order {order.Id}: {order.Status}";
    }
}
```

**3. Create the test project**

```bash
dotnet new xunit -n MyMcpServer.Tests
cd MyMcpServer.Tests
dotnet add reference ../MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj
dotnet add package Moq
```

**4. Write tests with a mock**

```csharp
using Moq;
using Xunit;

public class OrderToolTests
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task GetOrder_ReturnsFormattedString()
    {
        var mockApi = new Mock<IApiClient>();
        mockApi.Setup(a => a.GetOrderAsync(42))
               .ReturnsAsync(new OrderResult { Id = 42, Status = "Shipped" });

        var tool = new OrderTool(mockApi.Object);

        var result = await tool.GetOrder(42);

        Assert.Equal("Order 42: Shipped", result);
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task GetOrder_WhenApiFails_ThrowsException()
    {
        var mockApi = new Mock<IApiClient>();
        mockApi.Setup(a => a.GetOrderAsync(It.IsAny<int>()))
               .ThrowsAsync(new HttpRequestException("Service unavailable"));

        var tool = new OrderTool(mockApi.Object);

        await Assert.ThrowsAsync<HttpRequestException>(() => tool.GetOrder(1));
    }
}
```

**Key principles:**

| Layer | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `IApiClient` | Abstracts HTTP calls behind an interface |
| Tool class | Receives `IApiClient` via constructor injection |
| Tests | Supply a `Mock<IApiClient>` — no real HTTP calls |

**Alternative to Moq:** If you prefer no mocking library, create a `FakeApiClient : IApiClient` manually in your test project with canned responses. This works well when you have few methods.
